&lt;p data-preserve-html-node=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT ANELLO PHOTONICS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-preserve-html-node=&quot;true&quot;&gt;ANELLO Photonics &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.anellophotonics.com&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.anellophotonics.com&lt;/a&gt; is a leading-edge technology company based in &lt;span class=&quot;xn-location&quot;&gt;Santa Clara, CA.&lt;/span&gt; The company has developed integrated photonic system-on-chip and AI technology for next generation navigation.&amp;nbsp; At the core is ANELLO&#39;s SIPHOG™ gyroscope, based on its patented photonic integrated circuit technology. The result is a product that is higher performance, much smaller size and weight and power, at a fraction of the cost of traditional gyros used in industrial, aerospace and military applications (SWAP-C). Our products enable reliable and accurate navigation and positioning for manned and autonomous applications, including in GPS-Denied environments. Anello is currently shipping product to a growing list of customers in the Construction, Farming, Trucking, Unmanned Aerial Vehicles, Autonomous Vehicles, and National Security segments.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POSITION SUMMARY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ANELLO is seeking an experienced Senior FPGA Design Engineer to lead new product FPGA-based hardware development for advanced electronic products and embedded systems. This role requires strong expertise in FPGA architecture, RTL design, hardware validation, and board-level product development, including hands-on experience with PCBA design and system integration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate has a strong background and can lead FPGA and hardware designs from concept through production, working closely with electrical, firmware, software, manufacturing, and test teams to deliver reliable, manufacturable products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FPGA Design &amp;amp; Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, simulate, and debug FPGA solutions using Verilog, SystemVerilog, or VHDL.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop high-performance digital architectures including data acquisition, signal processing, communication interfaces, and embedded control systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate and optimize vendor and third-party IP, perform timing closure, resource utilization, and power optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support FPGA bring-up, hardware debugging, and system integration using standard lab instrumentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Verification &amp;amp; Validation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop simulation environments and verification methodologies for FPGA validation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform functional verification, hardware testing, troubleshooting, and root-cause analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create automated test procedures, validation plans, and supporting documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hardware &amp;amp; Product Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in schematic reviews, component selection, PCB/PCBA development, and board-level architecture decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate on high-speed digital design, signal integrity, power distribution, clocking, and EMC/EMI considerations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support prototype builds, manufacturing introduction, and production ramp activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
