&lt;p data-preserve-html-node=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Anello Photonics:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-preserve-html-node=&quot;true&quot;&gt;ANELLO Photonics &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.anellophotonics.com&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.anellophotonics.com&lt;/a&gt; is a leading-edge technology company based in &lt;span class=&quot;xn-location&quot;&gt;Santa Clara, CA.&lt;/span&gt; The company has developed integrated photonic system-on-chip and AI technology for next generation navigation.&amp;nbsp; At the core is ANELLO&#39;s SIPHOG™ gyroscope, based on its patented photonic integrated circuit technology. The result is a product that is higher performance, much smaller size and weight and power, at a fraction of the cost of traditional gyros used in industrial, aerospace and military applications (SWAP-C). Our products enable reliable and accurate navigation and positioning for manned and autonomous applications, including in GPS-Denied environments. Anello is currently shipping product and engaged in late-stage trials with various market-leading customers in the Construction, Farming, Trucking, Unmanned Aerial Vehicles, Autonomous Vehicles, and National Security segments.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inertial Measurement Units are a fundamental part of modern consumer, automotive, and industrial electronics. ANELLO is developing next generation INS and IMU sensor technology based on silicon photonics based gyroscope technology. The Sr. EE / HW Engineer will own critical aspects of the electrical architecture and implementation, ranging from schematic board design and layout to bring-up, debug, and validation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role you will help shape future ANELLO products with a strong sense of ownership and a product-first mentality. You will help identify opportunities and drive new ideas into action, through both hands-on technical work and thoughtful cross-functional collaboration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ownership of electrical product design from concept to delivery to manufacturing, proactively anticipating and addressing potential roadblocks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create interface boards and systems for manufacturing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage electrical engineering CAD tools and libraries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with hardware team to select components and write hardware design specifications for board level assemblies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design schematics and board layouts of medium to high complexity mixed signal PCBA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Sr ME to ensure board fitment, clearances, and thermal issues are considered during board layout&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Export accurate manufacturing info to key vendors to ensure board fabrication quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Export accurate BOM information to purchasing team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspect first articles for IPC610 workmanship&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with board bring up, debug and standard EE lab work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BSEE or MSEE degree with emphasis on Analog, Mixed Signal, and DSP Design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years’ experience with schematic design, ideally w/Altium for schematic capture and board layout&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in system designs from concept to mass production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with sensor integration including MEMS and GNSS RF design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Front-end power supply protection for products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication buses including RS-232, RS-422, CAN, Ethernet, SPI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of delivering working product at product-oriented companies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communications ski

