&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About ANELLO Photonics:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ANELLO Photonics&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.anellophotonics.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.anellophotonics.com&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a leading-edge technology company based in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;xn-location&quot;&gt;Santa Clara, CA.&lt;/span&gt; The company has developed integrated photonic system-on-chip technology for next generation navigation.&amp;nbsp; ANELLO&#39;s SIPHOG™ gyroscope is based on its patented photonic integrated circuit technology. The result is a product that is higher performance, much smaller size, weight, and power at a fraction of the cost of traditional optical gyros used in industrial, aerospace and military applications. It enables reliable and accurate navigation and positioning across many autonomous applications. ANELLO is currently engaged in commercial trials with various market-leading customers in the Construction, Farming, Trucking, Unmanned Aerial Vehicles, Autonomous Vehicles, and National Security segments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Sr Photonics Engineer will be responsible for conceiving and implementing experimental testing plans and identifying photonic design changes to continue to push the performance of Anello’s ingredient and product portfolio. We are looking for someone with a strong technical background and extensive laboratory skills in integrated optics. The engineer will play a crucial role in bringing PIC designs from prototype to product. As a key member of the team, you will engage broadly across the technical organization, including both software and hardware engineering, to work on the characterization and development of the core photonic system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and execute experimental plans based on a deep understanding of the optical system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect and analyze data, convey significance of results, and identify next steps.&lt;/li&gt;
